1.4 Slopes Vary Revisited

# Take 1000 random samples of size 250
set.seed(3)
n <- 1000
b1 <- numeric(n)
for(i in 1:n){
DF <- sample_n(bodyfat, size = 250, replace = TRUE)
mod <- lm(pct_bf ~ waist, data = DF)
b1[i] <- mod$coefficients[2]
}
ep <- quantile(b1, probs = c(0.025, 0.975))
ep
    2.5%    97.5% 
1.550538 1.841983
